    "Card games, notably Poker, exemplify stochastic puzzles where strategic skill is crucial.",
    "Simplified Poker variants require players to infer opponents' cards and calculate odds amidst hidden intentions.",
    "Gupta (2023) found that in Poker's preflop round, ChatGPT and GPT-4 grasp advanced strategies but do not reach Game Theory Optimal (GTO) play.",
    "ChatGPT leans towards a conservative approach, while GPT-4 exhibits more aggressive gameplay.",
    "Huang et al. (2024) leverage a Reinforcement Learning-trained OPT-1.3B model on all Poker phases revealing superior outcomes in win rates and efficiency, ultimately showcasing LLMs' adeptness at complex strategies in stochastic settings."
